Hey <@U026PLK4S> I just wanted to call attention to the completed sessions on Trent and my screens. We talked yesterday about how to make them cohesive and I think we landed in a good place, just minor revisions to the leading and type size.  

I’d like to also call out that the completed sessions on Om screen can be replayed while the completed sessions on the Re-Engage screen can not, they’re simply a summary.

<!channel> Hey design team! We met with the developers this morning to get a better understanding of what is needed in terms of a design handoff so they can build the designs accordingly and have some notes to share on that front and next steps in general - 

1. For dev handoff, we'll be updating the style guide to be dev friendly and cover global specs (like fonts, hex values, global margins, etc). Matt is going to handle this. 

2. Also for dev handoff, we'll need everyone to create a spec sheet for the key screen(s) in their section. So for example Ali will create a spec sheet for the Profile section, and the Settings section. Please include annotations for anything that isn't obvious from the comp (e.g. this section sticks to the top when you scroll). See Matt for further clarity on what needs to be spec'd or called out.

We also talked about priority in which the design tasks are completed, and here's the order we'll follow:
1. Finish iOS Comps
2. Create spec needed
3. Create any Android comps needed
4. Cut assets

The goal is obviously to get through that list for each section as quickly as possible, so knowing that there are a lot of moving parts, we listed these out for each section on a whiteboard so we can all track the progress. It's going to live next to the schedule on the project wall for the time being, so if you could either let myself/Jenna know as things are completed or check them off, that would be great!

Thanks for update on that front <@U026103R3>. Only immediate question I have is if for Android we’ll need to be cutting any 9patch assets. 

Both to that point and potentially in general, we may need to do some brush up on latest/greatest asset exporting. As we move forward through this, please know that it’s a safe space. We’re able and willing to help get everybody on the same page for the logistics of production. 

Thanks!
<@U0265G76F> we’re taking a look at the ios comps tomorrow to see what changes are needed for android. Would that be soon enough to talk about the 9patch question?
Yes :slightly_smiling_face:

updates on Library Dx for today. after talking to UX and further understanding the frequency/prominence of the “check box” version I went back to treating the Dx like before, just adding the extra elements like “I Made a Bowl” in the Level 1 header and adding hearts to sessions for favoriting

I decided to alter the play button instead of the image to create a more obvious indication of it being completed while not obstructing the image thumb any more.

Also included category lists, taking cues from some home detail work Phillip has done but also maintaining the 5 x 7 card ratio. Any opinions on if these should use photos or stay minimal like this?

oh and took a first stab at marking “I did my own” sessions, it feels partly there but I’m wondering if there might be feedback the calendar portion (i know we haven’t touch cal stuff yet, blazing new territory on this part)
